other_tests.procedure_name: CT ABDOMEN AND PELVIS WITHOUT CONTRAST
other_tests.findings: Dilated fluid-filled appendix measuring up to 12 mm in the right lower quadrant with minimal surrounding fat stranding. High density material at the appendiceal base may represent a developing fecalith. No evidence of intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation, focal lesions in liver, pancreas, spleen, kidneys, or any nephrolithiasis.
